_Nif’al_ Future Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_nif’al_ future tense]] follows these conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|| *Singular* |\<| *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | אֶכָּבֵשׁ<br>_ekoveish_<br>I will be conquered | \< | נִכָּבֵשׁ<br>_nikoveish_<br>We will be conquered | \< |
| *Second-Person* | תִּכָּבֵשׁ <br>_tikoveish_<br> You [male] will be conquered | תִּכָּבְשִׁי <br>_tikovshi_<br> You [female] will be conquered  | תִּכָּבְשׁוּ <br>_tikovshu_<br> You [males] will be conquered  | תִּכָּבַשְׁנָה <br>_tikovashno_<br> You [females] will be conquered  |
| *Third-Person* | יִכָּבֵשׁ <br>_yikoveish_<br> He will be conquered | תִּכָּבֵשׁ <br>_tikoveish_<br> She will be conquered  | יִכָּבְשׁוּ <br>_yikovshu_<br> [Those males] will be conquered  | תִּכָּבַשְׁנָה <br>_tikovashnau_<br> [Those females] will be conquered  |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎כ, ‎ב, and ש above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
